product: 3M 1110 Ear Plugs Corded, Extra Soft, Reusable Earbuds Noise Cancellation, Soundproof Earplug Use For¬†Underwater, Meditati...
title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
A wonderful product but not very durable
body:
I love these earplugs. Thanks to these I can sleep with my window open, or my bedroom door open and not be disturbed by early morning noises outside/inside the house. An absolute must-have if you are in the same situation.The only problem is they become all soft and useless after about two weeks of usage, give or take a few days. So, technically yes, they are reusable, but only to some extent. Been using them for 4 months, and I'm already on my 6th pair. Tried my best to reuse each one as much as I could, but after two weeks they become so soft that they decompress immediately, so you can't fit them in your ear.Not sure about the purpose of the cord provided with each pair, but it just leads to me pulling them out of my ears while sleeping, so I snip the cord and make them wireless :DThe noise cancellation is excellent, so long as you're not hearing truck horns 10 feet away or something - for mild to medium background noises, these work pretty well (fan noise, ambulance siren in the distance, someone washing dishes a little further away, or your neighborhood mosque's morning prayers - it can cut out these sounds well enough for me).Be warned - you'll need to turn your alarm volume all the way up, and still might not wake up. I'm sensitive to my alarm sound so I'm able to wake up at max volume - your mileage may vary.Will probably still buy more once I get through the first pack. Happy with the purchase.

product: 3M 1110 Ear Plugs Corded, Extra Soft, Reusable Earbuds Noise Cancellation, Soundproof Earplug Use For¬†Underwater, Meditati...
title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
Very good earplug, Value for money.
body:
Provided you get a good deal/price on Amazon(since the price fluctuates quite a bit) its a value proposition. Well worth the money.The isolation depends on a good seal so deep insertion is required for best results. With the proper seal its very good.Roll the earplugs between your fingertips to squeeze the memory foam, insert quickly and hold since the memory foam takes a second or two expand and grip the inside of your ear canal.When properly inserted the earplugs should not stick out. If they are roll them again and insert it deep and hold for maximum efficacy.When an ear plug seals at the entry of the ear canal, it creates a volume of trapped air between the entrance and ear drum. Because the first half of the ear canal is fleshy it can vibrate with mechanical input‚Äîlike with foot-falls or chewing on something crunchy. As the ear canal vibrates it slightly changes shape, and with changing shape its volume changes slightly, which causes the ear drum to move in and out to compensate for the changes in air pressure with volume change. This is called the occlusion effect, and it is why you hear your voice louder when you plug up your ears.With a deep insertion having an earplug that seals at the bony section, you don't have as much change in ear canal shape with vibration resulting in a significant decrease to the occlusion effect. With a 3M ear plug properly inserted you get less noise from your heart beat, breathing, foot-fall, or your own singing along...if you're into that sort of thing.It also improves isolation from outside noise. Related to the occlusion effect above, when you plug the outside entrance of your ear canal outside sound will still vibrate the flesh around the ear. This vibration will be coupled to the ear drum through the occlusion effect. With a deep-insertion ear plug sealed at the bony section, isolation from outside noise is essentially at it's maximum possible. There does remain some sound that gets to the ear through bone conduction, but there's nothing you can do about that short of clamping your skull in a vice.Bottom line: With these 3M earplugs deep insertion gets you the lowest noise floor and highest isolation possible.Background noises fade away considerably and are barely audible, you have to focus hard to hear them and yet you can have a conversation with someone sitting next to you or in the same room without the other person having to raise their voice or you having to strain your hearing.Quality memory foam so the same earplug can be used multiple times provided you have clean ears and minimal wax buildup. The firmness of the foam goes down a bit after the first use but it essentially stays the same thereafter. Comfort is excellent.Cons: The wire rope thing conducts noise(microphonics) when it brushes against anything which is annoying and a bit jarring. Solution, cut the rope only leaving an inch or two connected to either earplug to help in removing the earplug and enjoy the silence.

Here are a few reasons why I highly recommend this product:Durability: This shoe bag is made from very robust material that can withstand a lot of wear and tear. It feels solid and has remained in excellent condition even with frequent use.Design: The shoe bag features a modern and stylish design with a strong zipper and a convenient handle. It‚Äôs compact but roomy enough to fit my shoes comfortably, making it ideal for both travel and gym use.Versatility: This bag isn‚Äôt just for shoes. I‚Äôve used it to store toiletries, gym gear, and other essentials when traveling. It‚Äôs a versatile addition to my luggage.Ventilation: One of the best features is the ventilation. The bag has mesh panels that allow air to circulate, preventing odors and keeping my shoes fresh.Easy to Clean: The material is simple to wipe down and clean, which is essential after using it for gym shoes or hiking boots.Protection: It offers excellent protection for my shoes, keeping them separate from my clothes and other items in my luggage. No more worrying about dirt or scuffs.Overall, the Bold Fit shoe bag has exceeded my expectations. It‚Äôs a must-have for anyone looking to keep their shoes organized and protected during travel or at the gym. I will definitely be purchasing another one and recommending it to my friends.

I recently purchased this trolley bag for my travels, and I couldn't be happier with my decision. The multiple compartments and pockets kept my belongings organized and easily accessible throughout my trip. Additionally, the high-quality materials used in the bag's construction gave me confidence that it would withstand the rigors of travel for years to come.Overall, this trolley bag has become an essential companion for my journeys, and I would highly recommend it to anyone in need of a reliable and functional travel companion. It's truly a five-star product!"

product: Gear Turbo 45L Expandable Water Resistant Antitheft Laptop Bag/Backpack/Briefcase For Men/Women With Raincover (Grey)
title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
Value for money bag with good storage space
body:
Bought it for INR 1635. At this price range, I would consider this as a value for money product. I was mainly looking for a laptop bag that could double up as a travel companion for short trips and fit in as cabin luggage. This bag serves the purpose. Sharing my thoughts on the bag:Advantages (Pros or the Good part):1) Price (Value For Money): Similar bag from Safari and other brands cost above 2.5k. Got this for 1.6k, so good VFM2) Storage capacity: 45l is enough to store 10kgs (which is enough for 2-3 days trip). Also, this will fit in as a cabin baggage in flight, so the added advantage. There's also a bit of expandable storage, which helps3) Looks: Now this can be subjective, but overall I do not think anyone will call the product "ugly looking". On the contrary, this looks quite stylish4) Protection: This comes with a raincover, so can be considered as weather proofDisadvantages (Things which could have been better):1) Quality: Material of clips are made of plastic, hence might not last2) Cushioning: I feel they could have provided a bit more cushioning for back and the straps3) Rain cover: The raincover does not have Gear branding4) Compartments: There are just two compartments (a large one and a laptop compartment). I feel they could have provided at least one more additional front compartment for quick storage of small but essential stuffs5) Alignment of back straps: Not sure if this is the issue with my product only, but the two backstraps are not properly aligned in the bag I received6) Security: No security features like anti-theft Compartments etc.7) Tech features: No tech features like USB charging etc.Word of caution:1) I've not used the product thoroughly yet, so cannot comment on the longevity and reliability when used under rough and tough environment2) Please do not get confused with the number of cons outnumbering the number of pros, the product is a decent offering at an affordable price. Kindly refrain from comparing this product with other similar products which costs 2-3 times this product as their quality will of course be better than this.Conclusion: I feel this is a value for money product with decent built quality and ample storage. Hope it turns out to be durable and reliable as well in my upcoming trips.

product: Gear Turbo 45L Expandable Water Resistant Antitheft Laptop Bag/Backpack/Briefcase For Men/Women With Raincover (Grey)
title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
Just Awesome
body:
Purchased it during ongoing great indian festival in october 23 in 1395 rs and writing this review after one day of useIts an awesome bag in this price range and is absolutely a value for money item.This bag has huge capacity -- 45 litres andThey have tried to make  use of all available space which makes it very useful.It can be carried and used like a suitcase as well as it has a side handle and opens like a suitcase also if opened sideways. To hold the items inside it has extra straps like a suitcase so that they wont fall if its opened sideways. And this feature makes it super- useful (at least to me) as my work requires carrying all items and instruments that i require anytime when i m working. Also things can be organised very well. It has many extra straps all around which helps supporting the structure of bag ftom outside if its full completely.There are five sections. One chain for the small section in front to keep limited number of items.One central section is the biggest one which has enormous space. When this section is not filled much its size can be reduced by a chain. Third section is behind the second and is not that big like second but has small pouches inside.Fourth section is on the back surface of the bag which is in direct contact with your back. Its small but can be used as secret pouch for keeping money etc valuables.Fifth section is at the base of the bag and it contains the rain cover which can be taken out and used whenever required.Despite its huge capacity it does not look odd when i am wearing it on my back and looks like any other bag.Now lets see how long it lasts..

product: Safari RAY Polycarbonate 67 cms Cyan Hardsided Medium Luggage (RAY 67 4W Cyan)
title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
One of the standout features of this suitcase is its spacious interior.
body:
I recently purchased the Safari Ray 67 cms Medium Check-in Polycarbonate Luggage in Cyan, and I've been quite pleased with my choice. This suitcase not only caught my eye with its stylish cyan color but also impressed me with its overall performance.The hard polycarbonate casing of the luggage gives me confidence that my belongings are well-protected during my travels. While it's not entirely wear-resistant, it has managed to hold up well without any major scratches or dents, even after some rough handling.One of the standout features of this suitcase is its spacious interior. With a capacity of 57.6 liters, it offers ample room for all my clothes and essentials, making it perfect for longer trips. What surprised me is that despite its size, the suitcase is relatively lightweight, making it easy to maneuver and carry when necessary.The 4-wheel 360-degree rotation system is a game-changer when it comes to mobility. It glides effortlessly in any direction, and I appreciate how it makes navigating crowded airports and tight spaces a breeze. This feature has saved me a lot of effort and time during my travels.The number lock is another convenient feature, providing an extra layer of security for my belongings, giving me peace of mind when I have to check it in.It's also worth noting that this luggage is proudly made in India, which is a pleasant surprise for those who support local products.However, one thing to keep in mind is that the suitcase is not entirely waterproof. While it can handle some light exposure to moisture, it's not suitable for heavy rain. So, if you're traveling in wet conditions, make sure to use a rain cover or pack your sensitive items in waterproof bags.In conclusion, the Safari Ray 67 cms Medium Check-in Polycarbonate Luggage is a stylish, durable, and spacious suitcase that offers excellent mobility. Its minor drawback is the lack of complete waterproofing, but it excels in other aspects, making it a great addition to any traveler's essentials. Plus, the fact that it's made in India is an added bonus for those looking to support local products.

Title: Stylish Design and RFID Protection - A Solid ChoiceRating: ‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è (5/5)I recently purchased the HORNBULL Steve Green RFID Blocking Leather Wallet for Men, and I must say, it has exceeded my expectations. This wallet combines both style and security, making it a perfect accessory for daily use.The first thing that caught my attention was the wallet's design. The vertical layout is not only unique but also incredibly convenient. It easily fits into both front and back pockets, without adding unnecessary bulk. The genuine leather construction adds a touch of sophistication and ensures durability. In today's digital age, protecting our personal information is crucial, and this wallet offers peace of mind in that regard. The RFID blocking technology prevents unauthorized scanning of your credit and debit cards, safeguarding you against potential identity theft.The wallet's interior is well-designed, providing ample space for cards, cash, and even a few essential receipts. The card slots are thoughtfully placed and provide easy access to your most-used cards. The inclusion of a clear ID window is also a nice touch, eliminating the need to remove your ID or driver's license frequently.Pros:- Stylish vertical design that fits well in both front and back pockets.- Genuine leather construction adds durability and a premium look.- RFID blocking technology enhances security against digital theft.- Thoughtfully designed interior with well-organized card slots and an ID window.Cons:- The wallet's compact size might not be suitable for those who carry a lot of items.In conclusion, the HORNBULL Steve Green RFID Blocking Leather Wallet offers a winning combination of style and security. Its sleek design, genuine leather build, and RFID protection make it a must-have accessory for any modern man. If you're looking for a wallet that doesn't compromise on aesthetics or safety, this wallet is definitely worth considering.

product: Lino Perros womens handbag
title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
Detailed Product Review | After ~1 Year of Usage
body:
Lino Perros women's handbag is an excellent choice for those who are looking for a stylish and functional accessory to add to their wardrobe. This handbag is made from high-quality materials, including PU leather, which gives it a premium look and feel.One of the most significant advantages of this handbag is its spacious and well-organized design. It features multiple compartments and pockets that make it easy to store and access all your essentials, such as your phone, wallet, and keys. Additionally, the handbag comes with a detachable strap, which makes it versatile and easy to carry.In terms of design, the Lino Perros women's handbag is a standout product. It features a sleek and modern design with a quilted pattern that gives it a chic and sophisticated look. The gold-tone hardware adds a touch of elegance and complements the overall design.Compared to other handbags that are similarly priced, the Lino Perros women's handbag is a high-quality product that offers several advantages. Its use of premium materials, spacious and well-organized design, and stylish and modern look make it a superior choice over other similarly priced products.Overall, the Lino Perros women's handbag is an excellent investment for anyone who wants a functional and stylish accessory to complement their outfit. Its premium quality, versatile design, and modern look make it a must-have accessory for any fashion-conscious individual.

Pros and Cons ( 2 Months Use )
body:
Okay this will be my review for 3M corded mouse reduction earplugs.I live nearby a busy highway near to a city which can get really loud and noisy during morning 8 AM to 10 PM in a day. Those annoying honking and stupid bullet silencer sounds can really mess up your mental health and mood levels. Therefore it is advisable to use ear plugs for a quiter and healthy environment.Pros:1) Minimizes Noise levels to 80%2) Can be used for various Purposes ( Heavy Duty Drilling Work/ Studying / Outdoor Camping / Concerts / Sleeping ) I normally use it for sleeping at night.3) Cheap & Affordable4) Build Quality Is highly effective than other foam based ear plugs. I have used foam based ear plugs  previously but they usually got damaged after a month or so.5) Comes with the strings attached so it doesn't get misplaced. ( But it's for every type of ear plugs , foam or silicone. I don't get it why I listed it in Pros but why not :D )Cons:1) Not 100 percent Noise Cancellation2) Not advisable to use for longer 6-8 hrs as the inner ear starts to ache. (I personally think Foam based plugs do a good job at this)Other than that. I think these are pretty great but. You can go for it.

product: 3M 1270 Ear Plug Corded, Extra Soft, Reusable Earbuds Noise Cancellation, Soundproof Earplug Use For¬†Underwater, Meditatio...
title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
Great for motorbikes
body:
So, I was looking for ear plugs to use while riding my Speed 400. The bike itself isn't loud but the wind noise in my SMK Typhoon helmet (research says wind noise is inevitable in most, if not all, helmets) is quite high at speeds crossing 80kmph. Long term exposure to high wind noise will turn you deaf.I needed plugs that wouldn't totally drown out sound (horns, bluetooth helmet headset etc) but get rid of the wind noise. These work perfectly, most sounds are audible but the wind noise is muted.To insert the plugs comfortably, grab the top of your left ear with your right hand over the top of your head. Pull your ear up and front/ back (each ear is different) so that the ear canal is straight, making it easy to glide the ear plugs in. Vice versa for the other ear.

title:
3.0 out of 5 stars
Ordering the wrong size landed me in soup
body:
After reading a lot of reviews, I decided to purchase this product. As I wanted a good quality product I did not mind the price.The product had ergonomic features and the memory form was of good quality. I had purchased Large size for my Ford Freestyle. After a few days of use, I felt that the support was oversized and was causing neck and back strain. This was also distracting my driving. I was under the impression that since it was a new product, it will take some time for the body to get accustomed to it. But as the discomfort was not resolving, I decided to discontinue its use.I later contacted the grin support. They were very prompt in response and gave me many helpful suggestions. I tried following their suggestions but it did not bring full resolution.As it has gone beyond its return period, Im not able to exchange it for a smaller size.Overall, I think it's a great product and the support team is also fantastic but choosing the wrong size will end you in a soup! Try contacting the support team before you make the purchase to get the right guidance.

product: BANGE Multifunctional Waterproof Anti-Thief Sling Bag with USB Charging
title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
Perfect carry-on for people who travel light
body:
It's the perfect sized bag for people who always want to keep their essentials close while travelling. It's not bulky, doesn't get in the way, is hands-free and very stylish.I could easily carry a 500ml flat water bottle, sunscreen, medicines, wallet and passport when I was travelling with it. The bag has 9 pockets and 1 main compartment. You can choose to wear it on the front or back and the strap is also adjustable in length and has good padding.It does seem like it will stand a light drizzle, but I wouldn't trust anything during a full-blown rainfall. Better to just fit a tiny umbrella in it as well. :DOverall, It's a great carry-on bag which I feel is worth the money I spent.

title:
3.0 out of 5 stars
Ordering the wrong size landed me in soup
body:
After reading a lot of reviews, I decided to purchase this product. As I wanted a good quality product I did not mind the price.The product had ergonomic features and the memory form was of good quality. I had purchased Large size for my Ford Freestyle. After a few days of use, I felt that the support was oversized and was causing neck and back strain. This was also distracting my driving. I was under the impression that since it was a new product, it will take some time for the body to get accustomed to it. But as the discomfort was not resolving, I decided to discontinue its use.I later contacted the grin support. They were very prompt in response and gave me many helpful suggestions. I tried following their suggestions but it did not bring full resolution.As it has gone beyond its return period, Im not able to exchange it for a smaller size.Overall, I think it's a great product and the support team is also fantastic but choosing the wrong size will end you in a soup! Try contacting the support team before you make the purchase to get the right guidance.

title:

body:

But still purposeful for someone who wants compact dimensions. Given that people don't carry physical cash nowadays this is good... But if you are someone who carries more case then this does not work for you...IMPORTANT: It says RFID protected. But that is fake. I have a true RFID aluminium foil card protector pouch and I tested this wallet for RFID protection... Simply test by putting ur car key into wallet and see if your door request sensors open the car. If it's RFID protected, the car should not respond... But in this case it works... So NOT RFID protected....

product: Dell Essential Backpack 15 (ES1520P)
title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
The best 17inch Laptop Bag you can get in India.
body:
I own an Alienware Area-51m R2, which is a beast of a machine. I have been looking around for a bag that I could fit it in for a long time now. After months of trial and error I found this on Amazon. I was skeptical at first, because of the price. Alienware Vindicator 2.0 Backpack goes for around 8k when it's in stock and at the time, that was the only option which could actually fit the computer and the two power bricks that it comes with. But when I saw the awsome deal of 2.5k I was really skeptical.Well after using it here are my thoughts.It is quite capable of fitting a 17inch device in the laptop sleeve inside the bag, but since my device even though has 17inch display doesn't qualify as a normal 17inch device due to its huge butt üòÅ, so I tried fitting it in the accessory compartment next to it and it fits perfectly, so now I keep my laptop there and the power brickss in the laptop sleeve, no complaints. The laptop is protected by nice padding from around the bag and is made of really high quality materials. The zippers are really good quality as well. It has a lot of small organizers inside which you can use to keep other accessories like a pair of earphones, mouse, SD cards etc.As a bonus dell has also provided a raincover, which you can store in a sleeve below the bag  The raincover also acts as extra paddibg below the laptop when its is not in use, clever use of space there Dell.The design in the front illuminates when you flash light on to it, but if you really want to see how broght it can get you have to take it outdoors. When it's not illuminated it is so subtle you won't even notice it.Well, if there are any Alienware Area-51m or R2 onwers out there looking for a budget laptop bag, and if you're ready to compromise a bit about the arrangement inside, then you might be looking at a solid option. I would say go for it.
Read more

product: Safari RAY Polycarbonate Combo Set of Small,Medium and Large Check in- Cyan Hardsided Luggage (RAY 3P Combo 4W Cyan) (RAY3...
title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
One of the standout features of this suitcase is its spacious interior.
body:
I recently purchased the Safari Ray 67 cms Medium Check-in Polycarbonate Luggage in Cyan, and I've been quite pleased with my choice. This suitcase not only caught my eye with its stylish cyan color but also impressed me with its overall performance.The hard polycarbonate casing of the luggage gives me confidence that my belongings are well-protected during my travels. While it's not entirely wear-resistant, it has managed to hold up well without any major scratches or dents, even after some rough handling.One of the standout features of this suitcase is its spacious interior. With a capacity of 57.6 liters, it offers ample room for all my clothes and essentials, making it perfect for longer trips. What surprised me is that despite its size, the suitcase is relatively lightweight, making it easy to maneuver and carry when necessary.The 4-wheel 360-degree rotation system is a game-changer when it comes to mobility. It glides effortlessly in any direction, and I appreciate how it makes navigating crowded airports and tight spaces a breeze. This feature has saved me a lot of effort and time during my travels.The number lock is another convenient feature, providing an extra layer of security for my belongings, giving me peace of mind when I have to check it in.It's also worth noting that this luggage is proudly made in India, which is a pleasant surprise for those who support local products.However, one thing to keep in mind is that the suitcase is not entirely waterproof. While it can handle some light exposure to moisture, it's not suitable for heavy rain. So, if you're traveling in wet conditions, make sure to use a rain cover or pack your sensitive items in waterproof bags.In conclusion, the Safari Ray 67 cms Medium Check-in Polycarbonate Luggage is a stylish, durable, and spacious suitcase that offers excellent mobility. Its minor drawback is the lack of complete waterproofing, but it excels in other aspects, making it a great addition to any traveler's essentials. Plus, the fact that it's made in India is an added bonus for those looking to support local products.

product: American Tourister Polyester Hard 70 Cms Luggage(An6(*) 09 002_Black)
title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
Review After 5 years of usage (Limitted)
body:
Brief Overview:After a rigorous R&D of all kinds of huge trolley bags across Delsey, Safari, Samsonite (a clear out of budget segment I reckon) - this came out as a clear winner. Below are the high level Pros and Cons over the product:Pros:1. Extremely light and sturdy as mentioned and outlined in the Product description2. Its massive hence a lot of stuff that can go in.3. This product would be recommended for long haul and heavy duty haulage purpose4. The outer case is solid and very strong5. Look wise - Solid appeal as well.6. Mobility - All wheels movable 360* with good load carrying capacityCons:1. Since its hard case - there are certain challenges in fitting it into cramped spaces in a small car's boot space provided. I've always loaded it into a sedan (cabs) and drive a SUV - so never had an issue. It could be a struggle with a hatchback or small cars (very subjective)2. The wheels have a rubber coat which wore off after 4 years and the usage has been probably 10-15 instances in 4 years. Hence a bit dicey when it comes to this metric - since it should've lasted longer (again I could be wrong here - but yes)
Read more

product: American Tourister Polyester Hard 70 Cms Luggage(An6(*) 09 002_Black)
title:
4.0 out of 5 stars
Affordable Suitcase for College Students
body:
The product looks good but not impressive. It weighs very less hence can be used for flight travels.  It has an in-built three number lock system which is useful. Wheels are very smooth, even with good amount of stuffs packed in it. The handle is also smooth and feels durable.One side has a polythene sheet with zipper to close it incase. Other side has tie and clip lock to prevent clothes from falling while opening.  The bag is definitely water-proof because of the material built.One and only thing disappointing is the sturdiness. It does not feel hard enough to withstand a good amount of pressure. Even when we push a little, it flexes and returns. That does not feel good.Overall, if you want a good-sized suitcase for a price <4000 INR, then I think it is a reasonable one.

Stylish Design and Ample Space, But Quality Issues Persist
body:
Review of Skybags Backpack: Honest FeedbackI recently purchased a Skybags backpack, and while it has some positive aspects, there are a few quality issues that need addressing. Here‚Äôs my honest assessment:Pros:Design and Aesthetics: The backpack‚Äôs design is eye-catching, and I appreciate the overall look.Spacious: It offers ample space to carry my essentials, including a laptop and other belongings.Cons:Zip Quality: Unfortunately, one of the zippers is not properly stitched. This is a significant concern as zippers play a crucial role in securing our belongings.Strap Damage: I noticed damage on one of the straps. Durability is essential for a backpack, especially if you plan to use it regularly.Missing Skybags Tag: The absence of the Skybags tag on the inside raises doubts about its authenticity. All genuine Skybags backpacks should have this tag.Suggestions for Improvement:Quality Control: Skybags should pay closer attention to quality control during manufacturing. Properly stitched zippers and intact straps are essential for customer satisfaction.Authenticity Verification: Including the Skybags tag inside the backpack would reassure customers about its authenticity.

title:
5.0 out of 5 stars
Most strudy and functional bag
body:
I was using  victorinox sling laptop bag for almost 15 yrs which is still intact. Victorinox is a Swiss brand and know for quality and life time warranty. I wanted to replace with  a bagpack and was going for the same brand - however they are highly priced . While hunting on Amazon I came across Arctic Hunter and was impressed by their product and price range  - however was not sure about the quality of the product . Took a change and bought it - been using it for a month now - I am highlighting some points which would probably help buyers- Bag is sturdy and lightweight- has TSA lock and is theft proof.- Functionality- it has multiple slots inside - like for 13‚Äù laptop , Notebook , water bottle , small pouch provided for keeping tech accessories . There is a zip pocket on the right shoulder for keeping cash/ change/ cards which is quite handy  . There is a hook on the left shoulder strap for handing you sunglasses. On the rear side there is a hidden zip lock slot to keep your wallet / important cards .- Capacity - I carry a 13‚Äù Mac laptop, a note book , laptop charger , I phone charger , Magic  keyboard , mouse , mouse pad , pen , some papers , also I carry my lunch box ( flat tiffin) , 750 ml water bottle , a wind cheater , gloves , mask , keys .To summarise- this is the most sturdy hardback , waterproof and theft proof backpack . Has ample of space and multiple pockets to keep all the above . Shoulder and back cushioning is fantastic- even with putting all the above load , I don‚Äôt feel strained even after waking for kms . Value for money - Anyone looking for a branded and reliable product with all the above features should consider buying product from Arctic Hunter .All the best and kudos to Arctic Hunter
